The paper discusses a protocol for ensuring the validity of authoritative statements, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The protocol involves a decentralized network of witnesses, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of cryptographic multisignature methods also suggests a focus on cryptography (cs.CR) and security (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses the protection of clients' privacy, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
